news.title: Kotak Realty Fund invests over Rs 1,100 crore in The LaLiT's Bharat Hotels
news.para: The fund, a part of Kotak Mahindra Group’s alternative assets management and investment advisory business Kotak Investment Advisors, has invested in a hospitality company after more than 14 years.

news.title: EOW, Mumbai cops give clean chit to Pashmina Reality in cheating case
news.para: Ashok Mohanani, chairman of Ekta Housing, had in October last year lodged an FIR against Pashmina Realty and its directors Rajendra Singh, Kishore Koticha, Amit Jha, Preet Koticha and Rajesh Turakhia for inducing him to redevelop the prime property by presenting a rosy picture.

news.title: NRI businessman Jai Mahtani buys flat in South Mumbai for over Rs 83 crore
news.para: The deal for the apartment, spread over a carpet area of 5,211 sq ft, is valued at around Rs 1.60 lakh per sq ft, making it one of the costliest property transactions in the country. The buyer has paid Rs 5 crore in stamp duty charges alone for the registration of the deal.

news.title: MREAT orders Runwal Greens' promoter to pay home buyers for delayed possession
news.para: The MREAT has stated that an allottee is neither required nor expected to record that he accepted revised dates of possession without prejudice to his right to claim interest.

news.title: Gurugram: Orris Infrastructure accuses builder of cheating, Godrej Air buyers in a fix
news.para: In December last year, the court of an additional district judge had ordered to freeze 16 bank accounts of the residential housing project after Orris had filed a petition, alleging siphoning of funds by Godrej Properties.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram awaits nod from government for master plan prepared in 2020
news.para: Though finance minister KN Balagopal even proposes to shell out Rs 100 crore from KIIFB for the proposed urban rejuvenation scheme in the budget, all the cities, including Thiruvananthapuram, have prepared the draft as part of the AMRUT project, which called for the formulation of a GIS based master plan.

news.title: Capital announcement gives jolt to Vijayawada real estate sector
news.para: Realtors who invested huge amounts on developing ventures on city outskirts are in a limbo with the announcement, which is said to be a reality in the coming months.

news.title: Plots in Thaltej to be costliest in Ahmedabad
news.para: In neighbouring Bodakdev, where the jantri rate has been Rs 12,000 per sq m since April 2011, the new valuation is a mere Rs 24,000 per sq m.

news.title: Property tax in Ahmedabad to rise by 30-50%
news.para: Of the four-factor multiples in the carpet area-based property tax formula of the Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation (AMC), the ‘location’ factor is directly linked to the jantri rate.

news.title: Property tax collection system unfair: Yavatmal citizens
news.para: The civic body charges 1% tax at the time of registering sale deed. Now, the MC demands additional tax one percent tax if the owner wants to register the property with the MC, else the civic body refuses to issue any certificate, the delegation pointed out.

news.title: Crackdown against illegal sand mining in Odisha
news.para: Police on Saturday arrested 15 people, which included nine for attacking sub-collector Chavan Kunal Motiram and his driver Gagan Bihari Das at a place under Sahadevkhunta police station limits. Six others were arrested for illegal mining in Nilgiri.

news.title: New York Life Insurance to invest Rs 290 crore in Max Estates' SPV in Gurugram
news.para: Max and New York Life will be 51:49 shareholders in ABPL, which has a license to develop commercial project over an area measuring 7.15 acres located at Golf Course Extension Road, Gurugram.

news.title: TVS buys 5,023 sq ft bungalow in Bengaluru for Rs 20.93 crore
news.para: The property, with ground plus two structures, was purchased from Bengaluru residents PS Sanjeev and Anitha Sanjeev, according to sales documents shared by real estate intelligence platform Zapkey.

news.title: In five years, Haryana RERA helped deliver 2.5 lakh flats in Gurugram
news.para: "The vision of Haryana's chief minister was to bring relief to homebuyers and help boost the real estate sector. H-Rera's Gurugram bench has done that job well in five years. The authority will continue to do the good work," H-Rera Gurugram chairman KK Khandelwal said.

news.title: Damanis buy 24 luxury apartments for Rs 1,500 crore in Worli, Mumbai
news.para: The Damanis' sea-view apartments are in the Three Sixty West project on Dr Annie Besant Road and were purchased from the Sahana Group, which had formed a joint venture with Oberoi Realty to develop the property.
